Our first step is to include the variation of gravity with altitude. According to Newton’s law of gravitation:g_0(h) = G\dfrac{M}{(R+h)^2}

Where the subscript 0 refers to the spherical symmetry of Earth. The formula can be expanded at h=0:g_0(h) = g_0\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} (-1)^{n}\left(n+1\right) \dfrac{h^n}{R^n}= \dfrac{g_0}{\left(1+\dfrac{h}{R}\right)^2}

where we used the power series. We can call the term \left(1+h/R\right)^{-2} the altitude factor.
